quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,64,"Say, \"O owners of the book! come to an equitable word between us and you, that we will not serve (worship) anyone except God and we will not associate any partner with Him and some of us will not take others as Lords, besides God.\" But if they turn away, then say, \"Bear witness that we are those who have submitted (as Muslims)"
  3,65,"O owners of the book ! why do you dispute about Abraham, when Torah and the Gospel were sent down only after him. What ! then have you no sense"
  3,66,"Yes, you are those who disputed about that of which you had knowledge but why do you dispute about that of which you have no knowledge? And God knows and you do not know. dispute about that of which you have no knowledge? And God knows and you do not know"
  3,67,"Abraham was neither a Jew nor a Christian but he was upright, one who submitted (as a Muslim), and he was not of the polytheists"
  3,68,"The nearest among mankind to Abraham are certainly those who followed him and this prophet and those who believe, and God is the Guardian of the believers"
  3,69,"A party of the owners of the book like to mislead you, and they do not mislead (anyone) except themselves but they do not perceive"
  3,70,O owners of the book! why do you not believe in the signs of God when you are witnesses
  3,71,O owners of the book ! why do you cover the truth with falsehood and hide the truth when you know